1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,170
As part of a professional development program, I asked 13 trainees to closet themselves for one hour each day for two weeks.

2
00:00:09,839 --> 00:00:17,889
The trainees were asked to shut themselves off from all distractions and think constructively about anything that came to mind.

3
00:00:18,159 --> 00:00:26,529
At the end of two weeks, each trainee, without exception, reported the experience proved amazingly practical and worthwhile.

4
00:00:27,040 --> 00:00:35,650
One fellow stated that before the managed solitude experiment, he was on the verge of a sharp break with another company executive.

5
00:00:35,759 --> 00:00:40,770
But through clear thinking, he found the source of the problem and the way to correct it.

6
00:00:41,199 --> 00:00:47,250
Others reported that they solved problems relating to such varied things as changing jobs,

7
00:00:47,359 --> 00:00:53,009
marriage difficulties, buying a home, and selecting a college for a teenage child.

8
00:00:53,919 --> 00:00:59,969
Each trainee enthusiastically reported that he had gained a much better understanding of himself,

9
00:01:00,159 --> 00:01:04,050
his strengths and weaknesses, than he had ever had before.

10
00:01:05,119 --> 00:01:09,889
The trainees also discovered something else that is tremendously significant.

11
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:19,889
They discovered that decisions and observations made alone in managed solitude have an uncanny way of being 100% right.

12
00:01:20,159 --> 00:01:26,130
The trainees discovered that when the fog is lifted, the right choice becomes crystal clear.

13
00:01:26,959 --> 00:01:36,449
Managed Solitude Pays Off One day recently, an associate of mine reversed her stand completely on a troublesome issue.

14
00:01:36,799 --> 00:01:42,449
I was curious to know why she had switched her thinking, since the problem was very basic.

15
00:01:42,639 --> 00:01:44,369
Her answer went like this.

16
00:01:44,879 --> 00:01:49,009
Well, I haven't been at all clear in my mind as to what we should do.

17
00:01:49,279 --> 00:01:53,330
So I got up at 3.30 this morning, fixed a cup of coffee,

18
00:01:53,359 --> 00:02:00,130
and just sat on the sofa and thought until 7 a.m. I see the whole matter a lot clearer now,

19
00:02:00,239 --> 00:02:03,810
so the only thing for me to do is reverse my stand.

20
00:02:04,399 --> 00:02:07,889
And her new stand proved completely correct.

21
00:02:08,319 --> 00:02:15,810
Resolve now to set aside some time each day, at least 30 minutes, to be completely by yourself.

22
00:02:16,719 --> 00:02:22,210
Perhaps early in the morning before anyone else is stirring about would be best for you.

23
00:02:22,319 --> 00:02:25,489
Or perhaps late in the evening would be a better time.

24
00:02:25,759 --> 00:02:32,290
The important thing is to select a time when your mind is fresh and when you can be free from distractions.

25
00:02:32,719 --> 00:02:38,290
You can use this time to do two types of thinking, directed and undirected.

26
00:02:38,719 --> 00:02:42,770
To do directed thinking, review the major problem facing you.

27
00:02:42,879 --> 00:02:48,929
In solitude, your mind will study the problem objectively and lead you to the right answer.

28
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:55,090
To do undirected thinking, just let your mind select what it wishes to think about.

29
00:02:55,359 --> 00:03:02,610
In moments like these, your subconscious mind taps your memory bank, which in turn feeds your conscious mind.

30
00:03:02,959 --> 00:03:07,170
Undirected thinking is very helpful in doing self-evaluation.

31
00:03:07,359 --> 00:03:12,369
It helps you get down to the very basic matters, like, how can I do better?

32
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:14,690
What should be my next move?

33
00:03:15,439 --> 00:03:22,290
Remember, the main job of the leader is thinking, and the best preparation for leadership is thinking.

34
00:03:22,479 --> 00:03:30,319
Spend some time in managed solitude every day and think yourself to success.
